[[Very Reverend|The Very Rev.]] '''Graham Roy Barnett''' was the [[St. Peter's Cathedral, Hamilton |Dean of Waikato]] from 1927 until 1932. <ref>''[[Crockford's Clerical Directory]] 1975-76'' p55 London: Oxford University Press, 1976 {{ISBN|0-19-200008-X}}</ref>

Barnett was born in [[Nelson, New Zealand]] on 7 September 1885,<ref>[http://anglicanhistory.org/nz/blain_directory/directory.pdf BLAIN BIOGRAPHICAL DIRECTORY of Anglican clergy in the South Pacific]</ref> educated at [[Marlborough Boys' College]] and the [[University of New Zealand]]; and [[ordained]] in 1912. After [[Curate|Curacies]] in [[Ross, New Zealand]], [[Hokitika]] and [[St Mary's Church, Portsea]] he held [[Incumbent (ecclesiastical)|incumbencies]] at [[Tolaga Bay]], [[Te Kuiti]], [[Waihi]] and [[Frankton, Waikato|Frankton]] before his time as [[Dean (religion)|Dean]]; and [[Brighton]], [[Ifield, West Sussex|Ifield]] and [[Thakeham]] afterwards. Served as Temporary Chaplain to the Forces (TCF) in WW1. 
